{{see|monoceros}}

==English==
===Etymology===
First recorded by the [[astronomer]] Jakob Bartsch in 1624, but possibly created earlier by Petrus Plancius. From {{L.}} ''[[monoceros#Latin|monoceros]]'', a "[[unicorn]]"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Monoceros'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[winter]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[unicorn]].  It lies amid the [[Milky Way]], just east of the constellation [[Orion]].

